<div xmlns:perseus="http://www.perseus.org/meta/perseus.rdfs#" xmlns:dctype="http://purl.org/dc/dcmitype/" xmlns:tufts="http://www.tufts.edu/" xmlns:alph="http://alpheios.net/namespaces/tei" class="alpheios-lex-text_container en">
    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n2826" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐί̄ση</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ϝῖσος</span>), only fem. forms: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">equal;</span> epith. of
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">δαίς</span>, ‘equally divided’ feast, <i><span class="en">Il. 1.468</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; νῆες ἐῖσαι</span>, ‘balanced,’
          ‘symmetrical,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 1.306</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; ἀσπὶς πάντοσ᾽ ἐί̄ση</span>, i. e. circular,
            <i><span class="en">Il. 3.347</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; ἵπποι</span>, exactly matched in size,
            <i><span class="en">Il. 2.765</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; φρένες ἔνδον ἐῖσαι</span>, a
          ‘well-balanced’ mind, <i><span class="en">Od.
          11.337</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
